headline.print_headline: NASA: Cooling Pump on Space Station Shuts Down
headline.main: NASA: Cooling Pump on Space Station Shuts Down

results.snippet: NASA said Wednesday it was looking into a problem with a malfunctioning cooling pump on the International Space Station, but there was no immediate danger to the six crewmen on board.
results.lead_paragraph: NASA said Wednesday it was looking into a problem with a malfunctioning cooling pump on the International Space Station, but there was no immediate danger to the six crewmen on board.

headline.print_headline: Russia Bets on Sweeping Reform to Revive Ailing Space Industry
headline.main: Russia Bets on Sweeping Reform to Revive Ailing Space Industry

results.snippet: From rocket-shaped playground equipment to faded murals of cosmonauts, mementos of the heyday of Soviet space exploration are scattered around this sandswept town that launched Yuri Gagarin into orbit in 1961.

results.snippet: Russia successfully launched an upgraded version of its Soviet-design Soyuz rocket on Saturday, the Defence Ministry said, giving a boost to the country's troubled space programme.
